{"cursor":"6118","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Marc AllÃ©gret image = Marc AllÃ©gret & AndrÃ© Gide - 1920.jpg caption =\n| Marc AllÃ©gret & AndrÃ© Gide (1920) birth_date = birth_place = Basel, Basel-\n| Stadt death_date = death_place = Versailles, France othername = occupation =\n| Screenwriter and film director yearsactive = 1927 - 1970 imdb_id = 0002165\n}}\n\n'Marc AllÃ©gret' (22 December 1900 â 3 November 1973) was a French screenwriter\nand film director.\n\nBorn in Basel, Basel-Stadt, Switzerland, he was the elder brother of Yves\nAllÃ©gret. Marc was educated to be a lawyer. AllÃ©gret became AndrÃ© Gide's lover\nwhen he was fifteen and Gide was forty-seven. Later, Marc was to fall briefly\nunder the spell of Cocteau, who Gide feared would \"corrupt\" him.\n\nMarc's father, Elie AllÃ©gret, had originally been hired by Gide's mother to\ntutor her son in light of his weak grades in school, after which he and his\ncharge became fast friends. In 1895 Elie was best man at Gide's wedding.\n\nAfter filming a 1927 trip to the Congo with Gide, he chose to pursue a career in\nthe motion picture industry. His relationship with Gide ended after that trip,\nas AllÃ©gret found out that he preferred women after having experiences with\nCongolese women. They nevertheless remained close friends until Gide's death in\n1951. After working and training as an assistant director, in 1931 he directed\nhis first feature [[Mam'zelle Nitouche (1931 film)|Mam'zelle Nitouche]] and the\nfollowing year received much acclaim for his film, [[Fanny (1932 movie)|Fanny]].\nHe went on to a long career during which he wrote numerous scripts and directed\nmore than fifty films.\n\nAllÃ©gret is noted for discovering and/or developing new acting talent who went\non to stardom including MichÃ¨le Morgan, Jean-Paul Belmondo, Raimu, GÃ©rard\nPhilipe, DaniÃ¨le Delorme, Louis Jourdan, and Roger Vadim who would become his\ndirecting assistant.\n\nHe died in 1973 and was interred in the CimetiÃ¨re des Gonards in\nVersailles, France.\n","linknr":241,"url":"Marc_Allégret","recorded":1375070556,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Marc_All%C3%A9gret&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Marc_All%C3%A9gret&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/File:Question_book-new.svg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","/wiki/Wikipedia:Citing_sources","/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifiability","//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Marc_All%C3%A9gret&action=edit","/wiki/Help:Introduction_to_referencing/1","/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifiability#Burden_of_evidence","/wiki/File:Marc_All%C3%A9gret_%26_Andr%C3%A9_Gide_-_1920.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7b/Marc_All%C3%A9gret_%26_Andr%C3%A9_Gide_-_1920.jpg/220px-Marc_All%C3%A9gret_%26_Andr%C3%A9_Gide_-_1920.jpg","/wiki/Basel","/wiki/Basel-Stadt","/wiki/Versailles,_France","/wiki/France","/wiki/Screenwriter","/wiki/Film_director","/wiki/1927_in_film","/wiki/1970_in_film","/wiki/Screenwriter","/wiki/Film_director","/wiki/Basel","/wiki/Basel-Stadt","/wiki/Switzerland","/wiki/Yves_All%C3%A9gret","/wiki/Lawyer","/wiki/Andr%C3%A9_Gide","/wiki/Jean_Cocteau","/wiki/Be